summary: This document is an email chain from June 2019 between U.S. Marshals and Diplomatic Security Service personnel. It contains confirmation from Austrian police that Jeffrey Epstein's private plane (tail number N212JE), with Epstein and three unidentified female passengers, landed in Vienna, Austria on March 22, 2019. The group visited Café Landtmann before departing for Paris later that same evening.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Identified as the individual on the private plane (N212JE) that landed in Vienna, Austria on March 22, 2019, with three female passengers.

events.title: Epstein's Travel to Vienna
events.description: Jeffrey Epstein's private plane (tail number N212JE) landed at Vienna Airport at 5:00 PM. Epstein and three female passengers visited Café Landtmann in Vienna before departing for Paris at 10:00 PM the same day.

keyFacts: Jeffrey Epstein traveled to Vienna, Austria on March 22, 2019, via private plane (N212JE).
He was accompanied by three unidentified female passengers.
The group visited Café Landtmann in Vienna during their layover.
The same day, they departed Vienna for Paris at 10:00 PM.
The travel information was confirmed by Austrian police and shared among U.S. law enforcement (U.S. Marshals, Diplomatic Security Service) in June 2019.
